folder: Lafayette Avenue & Washington Avenue, Brooklyn, NY
text:
Lafayette Avenue, at the N.E. corner of Washington Avenue, showing an old Friends Meeting House, a Quakers' house of worship. It appears on atlas from 1880 on.

P. L. Sperr
View 1: July 22, 1934
View 2: October 12, 1940

folder: Lafayette Avenue & Washington Avenue, Brooklyn, NY
text:
Lafayette Avenue, north side, east from Washington Avenue. The corner building is an old Friends Meeting House as shown on Atlases from 1880. The low building on its right is a Baptist Sunday school and next to it is the Emanuel Baptist Church, at the N.W. corner of St. James Place. At the N.E. corner is the St. James Protestant Episcopal Church (triangular front).

P. L. Sperr

View 1: July 22, 1934
View 2: October 12, 1940
